	<!-- Magic Items -->
	<element name="Oil of Stealth" type="Magic Item" source="Ouroboros: Crying Potatoes" id="ID_OBC_CP_ITEM_OIL_OF_STEALTH">
		<description>
			<p>Applying this oil to a suit of metal armor or the joints of a metal construct removes that armor or constructs disadvantage to stealth for 24 hours.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Wondrous Items</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="type">Wondrous Item</set>
			<set name="rarity">Uncommon</set>
		</setters>
	</element>

	<element name="Concentrated Oil of Stealth" type="Magic Item" source="Ouroboros: Crying Potatoes" id="ID_OBC_CP_ITEM_CONCENTRATED_OIL_OF_STEALTH">
		<description>
			<p>Applying this oil to a suit of metal armor or the joints of a metal construct removes any disadvantage that the armor or construct has to stealth and applies advantage on stealth checks for 8 hours while worn or while the construct is active</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Wondrous Items</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="type">Wondrous Item</set>
			<set name="rarity">Rare</set>
		</setters>
	</element>

	<element name="Unstoppable Rod (CP)" type="Magic Item" source="Ouroboros: Crying Potatoes" id="ID_OBC_CP_ITEM_UNSTOPPABLE_ROD">
		<description>
			<p>This flat iron rod has a button on one end. You can use an action to press the button, which causes the rod to continue to move magically. Until you or another creature uses an action to push the button again, the rod continues to move at a constant speed and direction, even if it is defying gravity. 
			The rod can handle up to 8,000 pounds of opposing force. More force causes the rod to deactivate and fall. A creature can use an action to make a DC 30 Strength check, to deactivate the rod on a success.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Wondrous Items</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0">0 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="type">Wondrous Item</set>
			<set name="rarity">Uncommon</set>
		</setters>
	</element>

	<element name="Immovable Rod (CP)" type="Magic Item" source="Ouroboros: Crying Potatoes" id="ID_OBC_CP_ITEM_IMMOVABLE_ROD">
		<description>
			<p>This flat iron rod has a button on one end. You can use an action to press the button, which causes the rod to become magically fixed in place. Until you or another creature uses an action to push the button again, the rod doesn't move, even if it is defying gravity. The rod can hold up to 8,000 pounds of weight. More weight causes the rod to deactivate and fall. A creature can use an action to make a DC 30 Strength check, deactivating the rod on a success.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Wondrous Items</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0">0 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="type">Wondrous Item</set>
			<set name="rarity">Uncommon</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
